An ordinary walk home from school turns into an epic journey for Usato. After suddenly being dropped into another world with two fellow students, Usato learns he was summoned there by accident. But things turn around when he discovers a unique aptitude for healing magic! Now, he trains beyond human limitations, using his self-healing abilities to gain absurd strength and unrivaled stamina.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka V: Houjou no Megami-hen

The fifth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Goddess FestivalA fruit festival that brings the labyrinth city of Orario to life. Goddesses symbolizing fertility are enshrined on the altar, and among them is the Goddess of Beauty. Bell Cranel, who has survived and returned to his daily life from the dead depths of the dungeon, is here and ready to enjoy the bustle of the Goddess Festival until he receives a letter from a girl at a small bar in a corner of Orario"To Mr. Bell, please go on a date with just the two of us at the upcoming Goddess Festival. From Syr." Syr's single-minded determination will drive both Bell and the labyrinth city crazy. Meanwhile, the Einherjar, the warriors who claim to be the "strongest," are now suddenly on the move... (Source: HIDIVE) Note: Each episode streamed 1 day early on ABEMA and HIDIVE. The original TV broadcast started on October 5th, 2024.

After transmigrating into her favorite novel as Ethel Wallace, she realizes how ridiculous everyone is to fawn over Riena Cassius, her sister-in-law and the original female lead who regressed in the story. Ignored by the family and unable to endure the nonsense any longer, she is determined to divorce her husband and turns toward the marquis, Rienas future enemy, for help. Will Ethel escape House Cassius? Or will regression trump transmigration? And why does the marquis seem like a gentleman?
(Source: Tapas)

Guyangcheon betrayed the sect and became a demon under Cheonma. Living as a demon, he committed numerous evil deeds against his will under Cheonma's orders and ended up living a life filled with regret.
The Great Battle of Jeongma started by Cheonma. The long and hellish Great Battle of Jeongma came to an end due to Wisul-ah, who cut down Cheonma, who had even made the three great beings of Jeongpa kneel. Guyangcheon, who had been committing evil deeds as a demon, was captured by Jeongpa and tortured. While passing on information about the Demonic Cult to Wisul-ah with his last remaining conscience, he ended up dying due to Cheonma's prohibition.
However, for some reason, Guyangcheon regresses to the point where he first met Wisul-ah in the past. Realizing that the return was not a dream, Guyangcheon decides to live quietly so as not to do anything he would regret, but for some reason, the people he had bad ties with in his past life start to get entangled one by one, contrary to his intentions.
(Source: KakaoPage, translated)
